          "name": "Problem-Solving Framework",
          "description": "Structured problem-solving methodology that guides through problem definition, information gathering, solution generation, evaluation, implementation planning, and monitoring for systematic resolution of complex challenges.",
          "instructions": "Describe your problem with relevant background context. Specify evaluation criteria and timeframe constraints. The routine will guide you through systematic problem analysis, generate multiple solution options, evaluate feasibility, and create implementation and monitoring plans."
